                    "text": "[18]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF18"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "COVID-19, cancer patients and upcoming Ramadan"
        },
        {
            "text": "Beginning of the Ramadan is considered for reducing smoking among Muslims. However, only little studies have shown the effect of smoking on increasing the chance of COVID-19 [19] , more studies are needed in this regard.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 174,
                    "end": 178,
                    "text": "[19]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF19"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "COVID-19, smoker Muslims and upcoming Ramadan"
        },
        {
            "text": "3. COVID-19, Muslims with diabetes, high blood fat, hypertension, etc. and upcoming Ramadan A recent study revealed that, due to the treatment protocol, patients with hypertension, or diabetes, who are treated with ACE2-increasing drugs, are at higher risk for severe COVID-19 infection [20] . Due to the effect of fasting on Diabetes, Blood fat and Hypertension, rigorous studies are needed to find the effect of fasting on reducing/increasing the chance of a healthy person to becoming ill.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
